latestPosts.caption:
Something surreal happened last week - to even imagine that a young graduate who joined this company fresh from college exactly a decade back in September 2013 would end up being the first colleague to complete *TEN* years in this organisation 🏆

The odds that she would...

🔸stick it out through the crazy roller coaster ups and downs that this company has been through from nearly shutting down in 2015 to growing into what it is today

🔸reinvent herself and her role in the organization from starting off as an inexperienced customer delight executive and part-time makeup maven to creating the many many high-performing droolworthy products that SUGAR is known for today 

🔸would turn down the dozens of "opportunities" that kept coming her way across the years from so many many others who are building in this space to choose to continue, compound and conquer.

Vineeta and I have spent 1/4th of our lives building with you Mamta and for a change, we're struggling to put into words how much this means to us.

Thank you, for everything 🤗

Wish you nothing for the years ahead but what you have already brought to work for each day of the past 3,650 days... 

Grit, gumption and a whole lot of success in all that you build.

🌟🌟🌟

p.s. While most of the photos below are from the special day, the last one is from nearly a decade back at our first 300 sq. ft. office - where once a day, our dear housekeeping '𝘮𝘢𝘶𝘴𝘩𝘪' would shoo us out of the office and Mamta, being Mamta, would steadfastly refuse to vacate and climb up on some desk to keep attacking her task list 😅
